<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="411" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="411">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="411">
In the current collection, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Savigny" baseAuthorityYear="1826" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbricidae" genus="Aporrectodea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aporrectodea caliginosa" order="Opisthopora" pageId="0" pageNumber="411" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caliginosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="411">Aporrectodea caliginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in mixed species pasture. This species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. trapezoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="411" rank="species" species="trapezoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="411">A. trapezoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and they are found together mostly; however, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Savigny" baseAuthorityYear="1826" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbricidae" genus="Aporrectodea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aporrectodea caliginosa" order="Opisthopora" pageId="0" pageNumber="411" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caliginosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="411">Aporrectodea caliginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is less common (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5733/afin.051.0204" author="Plisko, JD" journalOrPublisher="African Invertebrates" pageId="0" pageNumber="411" pagination="289 - 312" refId="B46" refString="Plisko, JD, 2010. Megadrile earthworm taxa introduced to South African soils (Oligochaeta: Acanthodrilidae, Eudrilidae, Glossoscolecidae, Lumbricidae, Megascolecidae, Ocnerodrilidae). African Invertebrates 51 (2): 289 - 312, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5733/afin.051.0204" title="Megadrile earthworm taxa introduced to South African soils (Oligochaeta: Acanthodrilidae, Eudrilidae, Glossoscolecidae, Lumbricidae, Megascolecidae, Ocnerodrilidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5733/afin.051.0204" volume="51" year="2010">Plisko 2010</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first report of this species in this region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
